<br>
Like many mages I have been comparing the new 61-65 pets to the Epic Pet to understand which pet is best situationally.  I fully recognize that no one pet is the best in all situations; that was the way the game was designed, with 4 types of pets with different strengths and weaknesses.<br>
<br>
Of the lvl 61-65 pets, it is clear that the 62 Water Pet does the most damage if the pet can be positioned so he can backstab.  I recently parsed the Epic Pet vs. 62 Water pet in PoD and thought I would share the data.  I also have data from PoI, PoN, PoV, PoS, and CoD with similar results.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>This is a comparision of Epic Pet vs 62 Water pet</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
MOB’s fought: Underbulks in Plane of Disease, in the Grummus Castle courtyard.  Underbulks average around lvl 55 and are some of the best XP MOB’s in PoD.<br>
<br>
Parse was taken with the same XP group.  I started with the Epic Pet and then after 18 kills, switched to 62 Water for the next 18 kills.<br>
<br>
Both the Epic Pet and the 62 Water Pet had identical buffs:<br>
<br>
Burnout 5<br>
2 Fists of Ixiblat<br>
Belt of Magi’kot<br>
Muzzle of Mardu<br>
<br>
The tank (MA) for this group is a guild member of mine and knew how to position MOB’s so the pets could backstab.  Both the Epic Pet and 62 Water pet were directly behind the MA for all the kills.  I casted Malosini on all MOB’s and had no resists on my nuke damage so the assumption below is that all pet spells landed for full.<br>
<br>
Epic Pet over 18 kills:<br>
<br>
Time in Combat: 23:20 minutes (1400 secs)<br>
<br>
Total melee damage: 85,025<br>
Hit damage – 80,008 (94.1%)<br>
Bash damage – 3,624 (4.3%)<br>
Kick damage – 1,393 (1.6%)<br>
<br>
Epic melee DPS: 60.73<br>
<br>
Epic Pet did 68 procs of Wrath of Fire  = 68 x 118 damage per proc  = 8,024<br>
Epic Pet cast ElementalMasteryStrike 52 times = 52 x 84 damage per cast = 4,368<br>
Epic did 242 procs of ElementalMasteryBlast = 242 x 143 damage per proc = 34,606<br>
Total spell/cast damage done by Epic Pet = 46,998<br>
<br>
Epic Pet spell damage DPS =  33.57<br>
<br>
Total Epic Pet damage (melee +spells) = 132,023<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Total Epic Pet DPS = 94.30</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
62 Water pet over 18 kills:<br>
<br>
Time in Combat:  21:13 minutes (1273 secs)<br>
<br>
Total melee damage: 90,172<br>
Hit damage – 73,400 (81.4%)<br>
Backstack damage – 16,772 (18.6%)<br>
<br>
62 Water pet melee DPS: 70.83<br>
<br>
62 Water pet did 38 procs of Wrath of Fire = 38 x 140 damage per proc = 5,320<br>
(Note 62 Water pet is actually lvl 60 vs. lvl 49 for Epic Pet, so damage on proc is different)<br>
62 Water pet cast WaterElementalStrike 146 times = 146 x 140 damage per cast = 20,440<br>
<br>
Total spell damage done by 62 Water pet = 25,760<br>
<br>
62 Water pet spell damage DPS = 20.24<br>
<br>
Total 62 Water pet damage (melee + spells) = 115,932<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Total 62 Water pet DPS = 91.07</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
The damage output of the Epic Pet and 62 Water Pet are comparable, with the Epic Pet coming out slightly ahead.  Oftentimes in XP groups the MA doesn’t do a very good job of keeping MOB’s positioned so the Water Pet can consistently backstab, in which case, the lead for the Epic Pet widens.  As mentioned before, I have parsed similar results on other MOB’s in PoD, PoN, PoJ, PoI, PoV, PoStorms and CoD.   If the Epic Pet can land his spells, his damage output is unequaled. <br>
<br>
All my parsing leads to Jesari’s Pet Rules of Thumb:<br>
<br>
1) If you are fighting XP MOB’s that are lvl 61 MOB’s or below, and you need to provide DPS for a group (i.e., your pet is not tanking), use the Epic Pet.  It doesn’t matter if you are fighting in PoP, LoY, Luclin, Velious, Kunark or Old World zones. <br>
<br>
2)If you are fighting XP MOB’s that are lvl 62+, then use the 62 Water Pet for max. DPS.  This situation is most likely to happen in the PoP Tier 3-4 zones and some Tier 2 MOB’s.  Be sure to position the Water pet so he can backstab.<br>
<br>
3)For raiding, I use the 62 Water pet exclusively now.  Almost all raid MOB’s are lvl 62+, so the 62 Water pet moves ahead of the Epic.<br>
<br>
Now, I’m sure 90% of the responses I get will be from folks who disagree with me.  That’s OK.  It’s my data and my conclusions.  Use it in conjunction with your own research.<br>
<br>
